Dorothy Meyer https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorothy_Meyer 0 Dorothy Meyer (November 6, 1924 – September 24, 1987) was an African American character actress of film and television who made a name for herself portraying wisecracking maids, neighbors, friends, nurses, and church ladies throughout the 1970s and 1980s.
